See 'LICENCE' for details

The MB++ library is a TUI library, featuring menus, borders and animations.

The library contains a large collection of varied functionality and is used
by many MikeOS BASIC programs, including several on the disk image. This
program preforms no direct functionality.

Documentation on the library is avaliable through the wiki at: 
http://mikebasicplusplus.wikispot.org/

Requires MikeOS 4.3 or greater.
You can download it at: http://mikeos.berlios.de/mikeos-4.3.1.zip

This program requires the MikeOS BASIC interpreter. 
It may not work on MikeOS derivatives or OS independent
versions of the MikeOS BASIC interpreter.

